    "Proposition 3.16.",
    "The following two statements are equivalent.",
    "(i) For any bounded sequence ω j ∈ P d a subsequence ω j k and a potential form ω ∈ P d may be found in such a way that for every T ∈ P d,⟨ω j k, T ⟩ → ⟨ω, T ⟩.",
    "(ii) The operator I is surjective and a Banach space isomorphism.Proof.",
    "For λ ≥ 0, we denote by λB P d the ball in P d around 0 of radius λ."
